15 WHEREAS, everyone in Oklahoma and much of the world knows about
16 the horrific events that transpired in Oklahoma City on the morning
17 of April 19, 1995, when a terrorist blast ripped apart the Alfred P.
18 Murrah Federal Building at 9:02 a.m., claiming the lives of 168
19 individuals and leaving many others wounded both physically and
20 mentally; and
21 WHEREAS, we take this opportunity to remember those who died or
22 were wounded. May their lives never be said to have been in vain.
23 They live on in our memories, and their actions while alive
