1 infl uence and inform us to this day of how to live in charity toward
2 others and to do good and not repay evil with evil; and
3 WHEREAS, we acknowledge the debt of gratitude owed to the many
4 first responders – including local, state, and federal law
5 enforcement personnel, firefighters, search and rescue teams, public
6 and private medical personnel, other emergency services personnel,
7 and thousands of volunteers from the community – who immediately
8 answered the call of helping to rescue the living and recover the
9 dead. They saved lives, assisted the injured and wounded, comforted
10 the bereaved, provided meals and support to those who came to
11 Oklahoma City to offer assistance, and so much more; and
12 WHEREAS, we now renounce these despicable acts of terrorism and
13 ask Almighty God to root out the seeds of such terrorism that grow
14 in the hearts of men and women worldwide, festering into acts of
15 destruction and violence. We ask for an uncovering of such plots
16 before they can claim further lives. We ask for divine justice
17 tempered with divine mercy; and
18 WHEREAS; we repent on behalf of those who harbor such anger,
19 bitterness and hatred toward others. We ask for love to take root
20 in place of such darkness; we willingly forgive those who have hurt
21 us, and when we can't find it in our own hearts to forgive, we ask
22 for divine help; and
23 WHEREAS, we vow to teach our children and all future
24 generations that love toward their creator, toward themselves, and
